01:44:14,460 --> 01:44:18,100
[SPEAKER_00] But in the context of what I think are two big elephants in the room, right?

975
01:44:18,100 --> 01:44:41,399
[SPEAKER_00] One of them is the instant payments, which follows up on Cosman's point, which is that maybe if we – do we see this as a responsibility of the ECB to facilitate some kind of instant settlement mechanism in the digital world, a digital cash that does that?

976
01:44:41,399 --> 01:44:43,659
[SPEAKER_00] That's one of these contexts.

977
01:44:43,659 --> 01:44:45,039
[SPEAKER_00] That's one question in this context.

978
01:44:45,039 --> 01:44:56,699
[SPEAKER_00] And the other aspect is, in the context of privacy, it seems like we're talking about Monero, as it was just mentioned, as one extreme, completely in the dark, no regulation at all.

979
01:44:56,699 --> 01:45:05,380
[SPEAKER_00] But on the other hand, no one mentioned the Financial Action Task Force travel rule, which seems to be the, you know, a big elephant in this room, which is the other extreme.

980
01:45:05,380 --> 01:45:11,760
[SPEAKER_00] Everything is completely transparent and all the transparency is just determined ex post by whoever is in power.

981
01:45:11,760 --> 01:45:21,300
[SPEAKER_00] So, have you considered that there are projects like BIS Project Torbillon by the BIS Swiss Center that actually have one party who is anonymous and one party who is not?

982
01:45:21,840 --> 01:45:25,279
[SPEAKER_00] And other kinds of approaches like this do this problem.

983
01:45:25,279 --> 01:45:25,600
[SPEAKER_00] Thanks.

984
01:45:25,600 --> 01:45:27,819
[SPEAKER_19] Thank you.

985
01:45:27,819 --> 01:45:29,699
[SPEAKER_19] I think that all the questions are for you.

986
01:45:29,699 --> 01:45:30,880
[SPEAKER_19] Sorry for that.

987
01:45:30,880 --> 01:45:33,899
[SPEAKER_19] I need to recollect.

988
01:45:33,899 --> 01:45:35,119
[SPEAKER_18] What was the first question again?

989
01:45:35,560 --> 01:45:38,100
[SPEAKER_00] So, the first one is the instant settlement responsibility.

990
01:45:38,100 --> 01:45:39,300
[SPEAKER_18] Yeah.

991
01:45:39,300 --> 01:45:42,399
[SPEAKER_18] But I'm a bit puzzled there.

992
01:45:42,399 --> 01:45:55,920
[SPEAKER_18] So, there is the ECB already has a system, which is called TIPS, so where instant settlement can take place, which is, so that's already there.

993
01:45:56,399 --> 01:46:03,939
